{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "As depicted in subfigures (a) and (b) of Fig. 4, both DeGCG and i-DeGCG converge faster than GCG-M, achieving lower cross-entropy losses for both the first-token and the target sequence.",
    "Notably, DeGCG reaches a near-zero FT loss within 100 steps, whereas the one of GCG-M remains greater than 10 within the same steps.",
    "This indicates that the first-token optimization is noised and hindered by other optimization goals, degrading searching efficiency.",
    "Compared to DeGCG, the interleaved variant i-DeGCG shows higher FT loss but lower ST loss, attributed to the alternation between FTS and CAS, achieving a dynamic balance between these two searching stages.",
    "Regarding the ASR performance, shown in subfigures (c) and (d), DeGCG and i-DeGCG outperform GCG-M, achieving the best results within 300 steps, while GCG-M continues to underperform even after 500 steps."
  ],
